{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, it is equivalent to a behavioral model automating human actions.",
    "Its characteristics can be summarized as (1) automation and (2) non-random response to the environment (Dewey, 2008b).",
    "Regarding the first point, human instincts or initial habits are not formed in a linear growth, rather, they have the property of emergence.",
    "Once This automation is a result of emergence, a property that LLMs also share.",
    "When a stimulus (input) is introduced to the human behavioral model, the model (habit) responds accordingly (output)."
  ]
}